Operatives of the Osun State Police Command have arrested a 23-year-old man, Adeleke Sodiq for alleged robbery. The spokesperson of the Command, Yemisi Opalola who confirmed the arrest stated that Sodiq was arrested for allegedly robbing one Joseph Wusu at the Technical College area in Osogbo. Opalola also said Sodiq, who was also suspected to be a member of a secret cult, was arrested by men of the command’s Anti-Cultism Squad upon complaint by the victim. She said, “The suspect and his gang members have been terrorizing residents by forcefully withdrawing money from their accounts. “The suspect and his accomplices accosted Joseph on the road, compelled him to open his phone, checked his account balance, and forced him to transfer N150,000 to them.” She said the suspect has confessed to the offense level against him by the police.